{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, (17b) and the soliton equation (1) give Ric gB = -1 2 gB -1 2 (L X g)| H×H + h * g sym.",
    "Since X is vertical and A = 0, we have (L X g)| H×H = 0, thus (20b) follows.",
    "By 3.1, (ii), the image of h consists of nilsoliton inner products on 𝔫 with a fixed Ricci endomorphism β and a fixed volume density (by minimality).",
    "Lemma A.7 thus yields h: B → G/K.",
    "Regarding ρ *: π 1 (B) → Aut(𝔫), since it is the holonomy of ∇ ad, which makes the Ricci endomorphisms parallel, its image must centralise β."
  ]
}